  "title": "Civil Engineer",
  "description": "<ul><li>Reports to Construction Manager</li><li>Preparation of detailed schedule and monitoring the progress closely to ensure on-time completion</li><li>Preparation of detailed method statements and relevant documents</li><li>Coordination between client, consultant and sub-contractor(vendors)</li><li>Attend the meeting with the stakeholders</li><li>Generate and handle company reports, meetings and documents required</li><li>Propose alternative work method or other way to increase productivity</li><li>Handle technical and engineering issue</li><li>Ensure the activities comply with the quality, environment, health & safety requirements</li></ul><p><strong>Requirement :</strong></p><ul><li>Bachelor's Degree in Civil Engineering or Equivalent</li><li>Minimum 5 years of relevant Civil Engineering Experience</li><li>At least 2 years' experience in the construction & supervision of Vehicular structures and road projects </li></ul><p><strong>HOW TO APPLY:</strong></p><p>Interested applicants, kindly send your resume in MS WORD format or please click on “Apply Now”.</p><p>We regret only shortlisted candidates will be notified.</p><p>Important Note: Trust Recruit Pte Ltd is committed to safeguarding your personal data in accordance with the Personal Data Protection Act (PDPA).</p><p>Please read our privacy statement on our corporate website.</p><p>Trust Recruit Pte Ltd</p><p>EA License No: 19C9950</p><p>EA Personnel: Tan Sin Yong (Stella)</p><p>EA Personnel Reg No: R24124127</p>",
